Indian police on Wednesday arrested two men after eight near- simultaneous bombings killed 63 people and wounded 216 in the Rajasthan tourist city of Jaipur, the state's chief minister said.
Portuguese President Anibal Cavaco Silva voiced his disgust on Wednesday at deadly bombings in the Indian city of Jaipur.
It is with consternation that I learnt of the tragic and cowardly attacks perpetrated yesterday (Tuesday) in Jaipur," he wrote in a message of condolences to his Indian counterpart Pratibha Patil, released by his office in a statement.
